at|mitche:  Bidding:  East has a weak hand, 3 Queens (one of them singleton doesn't look very robust, even after a reverse).
There is a tool, the "Wolff signoff" that allows you to get out at the 3 level with a bad hand.
Basically, bid 2NT after the reverse.
