at|mitche:  With 10+ HCP and good support they use Jordan 2NT     1@S - X - 2NT.
The point here is to know what your agreements are over a double.
I advocate this treatment:     Jordan 2NT  
- a new suit at the 1-level is forcing (essentially ignore the X with 8+ points) and 
- a new suit at 2-level is non-forcing and not constructive, either.
- Redouble and spade raise generally shows 10+ and 3-card support.
-  1S - X - 2NT = 10+ and 4-card support   (rarely Hxx, where H = A, K, or Q)|
